        <body>       

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Aug 1888<lb/></p>
                
            <p>Atlantic City Aug 28th.<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> S Morais<lb/>
                Revd &#38; esteemed friend<lb/></p> 
            <p>Your note of 22d was forwarded to me to<lb/> this place&#44; where I have been over a week<lb/> with my wife &#38; family.  As to the Mr Davidson<lb/> matter&#44; I cannot say that I encouraged him<lb/> in the matter&#44; he simply wanted to know to<lb/> whom to apply for admission.  I know<lb/> nothing about the gentleman&#44; he brought me a<lb/> letter of recommendation from Manchester<lb/> &#38; wrote to me a Hebrew letter wherefrom I can<lb/> conclude that he has a good knowledge of the<lb/> Hebrew language.  Otherwise I know nothing<lb/> about his character.  He first requested me to pro&#45;<lb/>cure him a position as Hebrew teacher&#44; but know&#45;<lb/>ing the difficulties in this relation&#44; he questioned me<lb/> whether he can expect any supports as a<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>student of the Seminary.  He is a man of<lb/> rather quiet disposition &#38; has only been teacher<lb/> in England whence he emigrated from Russia.<lb/>  I agree with you that we should endeavor<lb/> to encourage young Americans for our<lb/> cause rather than old foreigners who enter<lb/> the field for want of something better to do.<lb/>  On my return after to&#45;morrow I shall<lb/> most readily comply with your request<lb/> &#38; examine him as to his abilities in Hebrew<lb/> grammar &#38; Biblical history.  I know<lb/> that his profane education is limited.<lb/></p>
            <p>My d wife has been suffering from nervous<lb/> prostration &#38; was advised to come to the sea&#45;<lb/>side to get strength and quiet&#59; I have been<lb/> here 12 days in order to keep her company &#38;<lb/> am anxious to get home.<lb/></p>
            <p>With most sincere wishes to yourself and<lb/> respected family &#38; most hearty &#91;Hebrew&#93;<lb/></p>
            <p>I remain yours fraternally<lb/> H W Schneeberger<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
